Crevasse

Challenging the Crevasse
Access the Crevasse through the Events button on the world map.

*Note that it is not possible to call on friends for support in the Crevasse.
Codes
Codes are rules that may affect both characters and enemies in the Crevasse.

In each quest, you can select and activate up to 6 codes from the list of available codes.


Codes can restrict which characters you may bring into battle, and may enhance your enemies among other effects.

Tap and hold on a code to see the details on its effects.
Selected codes will be displayed under the Code tab of each quest's preparation screen. They may also be reviewed in the pause menu during a quest.

Do note that codes take effect the moment you begin a quest, and codes cannot be removed in battle!
Special Countdown Cards
Some quests may feature Special Countdown cards.

Special Countdown cards are codes that replace the special countdown conditions of all enemies in the quest.

Unlike normal codes, you may only activate one Special Countdown card per quest!

Force Weakness Cards and Additional Force Gauge Effects Cards
Some quests may feature Force Weakness cards and Additional Force Gauge Effects cards.

Force Weakness cards are codes that replace the force weakness conditions of all enemies in the quest.

Additional Force Gauge Effects cards are codes that allow adding of extra force gauge effects for all enemies in the quest.

Similar to Special Countdown cards, you may only activate one Force Weakness card and one Additional Force Gauge Effects card per quest!


Status
Clearing all of a quest's missions as well as its target score in the same attempt will award a status for that quest.

The characters and codes used in a quest cleared to cannot be used in any other quests in the same Crevasse event.


Characters and codes used in clearing a quest to will be subject to engagement restrictions.

If a character with engagement restrictions is used to clear another quest within the Crevasse event, the status of the previously cleared quest will be reset, and the points awarded to the quest will be reset to 0.

*Before beginning another quest with a character subject to engagement restrictions, a message will display to confirm any quests that will have their status reset.

Saving of Codes across Quests
You may save your most recent set of selected codes by tapping the Save button after editing codes.



When entering a quest, saved codes that are applicable for the current quest difficulty will be loaded in as selected codes.

Do note that codes subject to engagement restrictions in another quest will be automatically removed from the list. If selected codes exceed the limit of codes allowed for the quest, extra codes will be removed to fit.

All saved codes will be reset upon clearing any quest to .

Crevasse Points
Upon clearing the quest to , points are awarded according to the combination of codes activated.

Quests may also have extra multipliers for the points awarded based on the difficulty level.
Removing the status of a quest will set the points awarded for that quest back to 0, reducing the total points gained for the event. However, codes and characters used for that quest will also become usable again.

Event missions that were already cleared will remain cleared.

Accumulate as many points as possible across all the Crevasse quests by using codes and clearing quests to !

Receiving Crevasse Rewards
Collect rewards based on the total points reached in the Missions page.
